when you emit the following tailwind code:
```css
@utility sidebar-footer-item {
    @apply flex items-center gap-3 cursor-pointer;
    @apply text-sm;
    color: rgb(var(--color-text-muted));
    padding: theme(spacing.[1.5]) theme(spacing.[3]);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    @variant hover {
        color: rgb(var(--color-text-base));
        background-color: rgb(var(--color-muted-rgb) / var(--alpha-muted-hover));
    }
}
```

It produces the following output:
```css
@utility sidebar-footer-item {
  @apply flex items-center gap-3 cursor-pointer; @apply text-sm; color: rgb(var(--color-text-muted)) ; padding: theme(spacing. [1.5]) theme(spacing. [3]) ; border-radius: var(--radius-md) ; @variant hover { color: rgb(var(--color-text-base)) ; background-color: rgb(var(--color-muted-rgb) / var(--alpha-muted-hover)) ; }
}
```

Looks ok until you look at the function code of spacing `theme(spacing. [1.5]) ` It has a space between the . and the [1.5] it should be `theme(spacing.[1.5]) `. 


I'm not sure if this is a rslib issue or a tailwind issue
